(1960, 1, '2018-06-16 11:35:54', '2018-06-16 11:35:54', 'Welcome to Partnership for Better Health Organization (PBH), a Cambodian NGO that work to strengthen health system and improve quality of health and social services in Cambodia.\r\n\r\nPartnership for Better Health created and approved by Ministry of Interior on 22 October 2012. Partnership for Better Health initiated by at least 100 health professional and expert staff who have great health experiences and legacy works in Cambodia. Our dedicated team of experts and professional staff are committed to enriching quality of health care and social services and better health care system in Cambodia.\r\n\r\nIn collaboration with the Ministry of Health, other Ministries and Health Development Partners, we have developed and implemented a number of innovative and responsive programs and services that promote and support for health care and social services, health care quality and better health system and that also reflect the variety of different lesson learned, experiences, interests and team work cultures.\r\n\r\nPartnership for Better Health consists of a dedicated team who has high skills and expertise in health system strengthening work in Cambodia since 2000.\r\n\r\nOur primary goals dovetail with the mission of the Ministry of Health as stated in the Cambodian Health Strategic Plan 2008-2015 (HSP2) "to provide stewardship for the entire health sector and to ensure a supportive environment for increased demand and equitable access to quality health services in order that all the peoples of Cambodia are able to achieve the highest level of health and well-being. Our other goal is to improve quality of health and social services.\r\n\r\nPartnership for Better Health recognizes that a good health services are those which deliver effective, safe, quality health interventions to those who need them, when and where needed. A health system encompasses the total of all the organizations, institutions and resources whose primary purpose is to improve health.\r\n\r\nOn the other hand a health system needs staff, funds, information, supplies, transport, communications and overall guidance and direction. Partnership for Better Health will work to strengthen a health system that will provide services that are effective at improving health and health equity, responsive to people\'s needs and desires, financially fair, and use resources efficiently. By doing so, Partnership for Better Health believe that will improves people\'s lives tangibly every day – whether it is providing a good quality of health care and social service within a good health system.\r\n\r\nPartnership for Better Health\'s principal is "universal access to quality health services for all" cannot be achieved without the development of a robust health system. Health systems are inherently complex. Work in one area without regard to other parts of the system will may not improve total system performance. Even if only one aspect is tackled, an awareness of the needs of the whole of system approach is necessary.\r\n\r\nAs a team of Partnership for Better Health, we are expected to collaborate with governmental organizational and health development partner leadership for ensuring the continued innovative and development of the Health Systems Strengthening in Cambodia.', 'Welcome', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '1957-autosave-v1', '', '', '2018-06-16 11:35:54', '2018-06-16 11:35:54', '', 1957, 'http://localhost/bkpbhcam/2018/06/16/1957-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
