(2018, 1, '2018-06-23 09:04:39', '2018-06-23 09:04:39', 'Partnership for Better Health (PBH) through URC-PBH sub-agreement No: FY14-G01-7017 under USAID Quality Health Services Project, AID-442-A-14-0003, employs the key six staff who work under this project.\r\n\r\nPBH under the USAID Quality Health Services project will continue to contribute to the Royal Government of Cambodia’s (RGC) impressive achievements in maternal, newborn, and child survival. The project will strive to reduce neonatal mortality, improve childhood nutrition, improve access to and quality of family planning (FP), and to further decrease maternal, infant and child deaths. Together with our partners we will tackle the unfinished reproductive, maternal, newborn, child health and nutrition (RMNCHN) agenda in Cambodia over the next five years Jan 20, 2014 to Jan 16, 2019.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nPartnership for Better Health (PBH) through this sub-agreement will participate in this project and contribute to these goals by filling a key staff position of Monitoring &amp; Evaluation advisor, Dr. Troeng Panhacharun, three  Monitoring &amp; Evaluation advisor officers and two programmers.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nPBH will provide technical assistance in the improvement of data collection on health system performance.\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Oversee data collection and reporting of program performance indicators.</li>\r\n 	<li>Lead the implementation of baseline, follow-up and evaluation studies.</li>\r\n 	<li>Ensure availability and quality of routine performance monitoring data.</li>\r\n 	<li>Synthesize data on project performance and RMNCHN developments into user-friendly reports and</li>\r\n 	<li>advocacy briefs to facilitate use by project management, RGC, and other partners.</li>\r\n 	<li>Train partners in research and evaluation methods</li>\r\n</ul>', 'PBH under USAID Quality Health Services Project', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'pbh-under-usaid-quality-health-services-project', '', '', '2018-06-23