(2036, 1, '2018-06-23 09:41:07', '2018-06-23 09:41:07', '[vc_row full_width="stretch_row" type="vc_default"][vc_column width="1/4"][vc_single_image source="featured_image" img_size="large"][vc_btn title="Download publication" color="primary" i_icon_fontawesome="fa fa-arrow-down" add_icon="true" link="url:http%3A%2F%2Fupprcambodia.org%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F02%2F1433429386-pin-cambodia-2014-alternative-site-planning-in-phnom-penh.pdf||target:%20_blank|"][/vc_column][vc_column width="3/4" css=".vc_custom_1528444671900{margin-left: 20px !important;}"][vc_custom_heading text="ALTERNATIVE SITE PLANNING in Chrang Chamreh, Cambodia" font_container="tag:h4|text_align:left" google_fonts="font_family:Roboto%3A100%2C100italic%2C300%2C300italic%2Cregular%2Citalic%2C500%2C500italic%2C700%2C700italic%2C900%2C900italic|font_style:400%20regular%3A400%3Anormal"][vc_column_text]<strong>Publisher:</strong> People in Need Cambodia\r\n\r\n<strong>Publication Date:</strong> 2014\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">In 2013, People in Need (PIN) and its local partner Sahmakum Teang Tnaut (STT) received a grant from European Union and Czech Development Agency to implement a project focusing on alternative spatial planning in urban poor areas of Phnom Penh.\r\nPIN &amp; STT engaged the architecture practice, Collective Studio to propose alternative re-development options for\r\nthese villages. The objective was to avoid re-location and offer an on-site solution acceptable to residents, local authorities and other stakeholders.</p>\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row]', 'publication3', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'publication3', '', '', '2018-06-23 09:41:24', '2018-06-23 09:41:24', '', 0, 'http://localhost/bkpbhcam/?p=2036', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(2037, 1, '2018-06-23 09:32:53', '2018-06-23 09:32:53', 'July 8, 2014 at DAI meeting rooms\r\n\r\nBy Dr Mean Reatanak Sambath, PBH Executive Director\r\n\r\nAs AeHIN working council, Dr Mean Reatanak Sambath, PBH Executive Director, organized a first meeting of Cambodian eHealth Information Network (CAMEHIN) on July 8, 2014 at DAI meeting room. A total of 18 persons attended the meeting, 6 of them are from governmental institution and 12 of them are from NGOs. The participation are from Ministry of Health, Ministry of Interior, National Centre for HIV/AIDS, Dermatology and STD Control (NCHADS), Medical Council of Cambodia, Partnership for Better Health, Open Institute, INSTEED, Social Health Protection Association (SHPA), Development Innovation (DAI) and Information Technology Skill - ITS Center. The objective of the meeting is to building and reinforce a function of Cambodian eHealth Information Network under umbrella of AeHIN mandate and AeHIN implementation plan. Dr Sambath facilitated and presented during the meeting. Key topics were discussed during the meeting such as what will priority and action for CAMEHIN and how to make our network is functioning. Dr Sambath also presented a results of AeHIN implementation since 2010. After active discussion, team members agreed to run and make CAMEHIN function. The team agreed to add more members of health and none health sector. The team also agreed to have Cambodia AeHIN hours or call CAMEHIN hours. Team members will assist to share CAMEHIN information to other members and/or network. Team members shared their activities related to', 'First meeting of Cambodian eHealth Information Network', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'first-meeting-of-cambodian-ehealth-information-network', '', '', '2018-06-24 01:30:13', '2018-06-24 01:30:13', '', 0, 'http://localhost/bkpbhcam/?p=2037', 0, 'post', '', 0),
