(2055, 1, '2018-06-23 12:06:13', '2018-06-23 12:06:13', '<div>\r\n<h3><strong>JOB AND CAREER</strong></h3>\r\nPartnership for Better Health (PBH) is working with the USAID Social Health Protection Project and Quality Health Services Project to support the Ministry of Health through increasing demand and equitable access to quality healthcare services in Cambodia.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="bg_job_color">\r\n\r\n<strong>Health Equity Fund Monitors</strong>\r\nThrough USAID Social Health Protection Project, PBH is looking for 1 (One) appropriately qualified national candidates to fill the positions of Database Programmer who will based in Phnom Penh (1 Position).\r\n\r\nThe selected candidates will work under the supervision of the Health Informatics Team Leader, and she/he will be responsible for system development and support.\r\n\r\n<strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Develop and maintain Patient Management and Registration System</li>\r\n 	<li>Develop and maintain Project Database System</li>\r\n 	<li>Provide system support to end-users</li>\r\n 	<li>Reports to Health Informatics Team Leader</li>\r\n 	<li>Perform other tasks as required</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Qualifications and Requirements:</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Cambodian national</li>\r\n 	<li>Bachelor degree of Computer Science/Information Technology or equivalent</li>\r\n 	<li>3 years experienced developing web-based applications</li>\r\n 	<li>2 years experienced programming in PHP and MySQL</li>\r\n 	<li>Experienced with PHP MVC Framework</li>\r\n 	<li>Experienced in writing web standards/cross browser HTML and CSS</li>\r\n 	<li>Good communication skill in English and Khmer</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nThe deadline for applications is <u>Jan 13th, 2017</u>. All interested candidates can submit their applications by sending CV and cover letter indicating working station as above mentioned to: hr@pbhcam.org or submit a hard copy to the PBH offices on the 3rd floor, # 10, street 214, Sangkat Chey Chum Neas, Khan Daun Penh, Phnom Penh, Cambodia. Women are encouraged to apply. Only shortlisted applicants will be contacted.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="bg_job">\r\n\r\n<strong>Health Equity Fund Monitors</strong>\r\nThrough USAID Social Health Protection Project, PBH is looking for 1 (One) appropriately qualified national candidates to fill the positions of Health Equity Fund Monitor who will based in Preah Vihear (1 Position). The selected candidates will work under the supervision of the Health Financing Technical Officers, and she/he will be responsible for monitoring ongoing Health Equity Fund (HEF) activities in their target areas.\r\n\r\n<strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Oversee HEF Contract implementation based on established evaluation methodology.</li>\r\n 	<li>On a monthly basis, monitor HEF activities are given area using the tools and methodologies of the HEF system.</li>\r\n 	<li>Conduct household interviews and review of HEF documentation entering results into a computerized reporting database.</li>\r\n 	<li>Create a monthly report of findings related to monitoring of HEF activities according to the standard format required.</li>\r\n 	<li>Perform other tasks as required.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Qualifications and Requirements:</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Completed Bachelor Degree or at least 2 years experiences</li>\r\n 	<li>Computer skills (Word, Excel, PowerPoint)</li>\r\n 	<li>Communication skill in English and Khmer</li>\r\n 	<li>Experience in data collection and/or assisting in any research/survey</li>\r\n 	<li>Strong interpersonal skills, demonstrated ability to work well with the poor and rural areas</li>\r\n 	<li>Analytical skills, Self-motivated and results oriented</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nThe deadline for applications is <b><u>Dec 21th, 2016</u></b>. All interested candidates can submit their applications by sending CV and cover letter indicating working station as above mentioned to: hr@pbhcam.org or submit a hard copy to the PBH offices on the 3rd floor, # 10, street 214, Sangkat Chey Chum Neas, Khan Daun Penh, Phnom Penh, Cambodia. Women are encouraged to apply. Only shortlisted applicants will be contacted.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="bg_job_color">\r\n\r\n<strong>Health Equity Fund Monitors</strong>\r\nThrough USAID Social Health Protection Project, PBH is looking for 1 (One) appropriately qualified national candidates to fill the positions of Health Equity Fund Monitor who will based in Kandal (1 Position).\r\n\r\nThe selected candidates will work under the supervision of the Health Financing Technical Officers, and she/he will be responsible for monitoring ongoing Health Equity Fund (HEF) activities in their target areas.\r\n\r\n<strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Oversee HEF Contract implementation based on established evaluation methodology.</li>\r\n 	<li>On a monthly basis, monitor HEF activities are given area using the tools and methodologies of the HEF system.</li>\r\n 	<li>Conduct household interviews and review of HEF documentation entering results into a computerized reporting database.</li>\r\n 	<li>Create a monthly report of findings related to monitoring of HEF activities according to the standard format required.</li>\r\n 	<li>Perform other tasks as required.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Qualifications and Requirements:</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Completed Bachelor Degree or at least 2 years experiences</li>\r\n 	<li>Computer skills (Word, Excel, PowerPoint)</li>\r\n 	<li>Communication skill in English and Khmer</li>\r\n 	<li>Experience in data collection and/or assisting in any research/survey</li>\r\n 	<li>Strong interpersonal skills, demonstrated ability to work well with the poor and rural areas</li>\r\n 	<li>Analytical skills, Self-motivated and results oriented</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nThe deadline for applications is <u>September 19th, 2016</u>. All interested candidates can submit their applications by sending CV and cover letter indicating working station as above mentioned to: hr@pbhcam.org or submit a hard copy to the PBH offices on the 3rd floor, # 10, street 214, Sangkat Chey Chum Neas, Khan Daun Penh, Phnom Penh, Cambodia. Women are encouraged to apply. Only shortlisted applicants will be contacted.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="bg_job">\r\n\r\n<strong>Health Equity Fund Monitors</strong>\r\nThrough USAID Social Health Protection Project, PBH is looking for 3 (Three) appropriately qualified national candidates to fill the positions of Health Equity Fund Monitor who will based in Bantheay Mean Chey (1 position) , Phnom Penh (1 Position) and Pursat (1 Position).\r\nThe selected candidates will work under the supervision of the Health Financing Technical Officers, and she/he will be responsible for monitoring ongoing Health Equity Fund (HEF) activities in their target areas.\r\n\r\n<strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Oversee HEF Contract implementation based on established evaluation methodology.</li>\r\n 	<li>On a monthly basis, monitor HEF activities are given area using the tools and methodologies of the HEF system.</li>\r\n 	<li>Conduct household interviews and review of HEF documentation entering results into a computerized reporting database.</li>\r\n 	<li>Create a monthly report of findings related to monitoring of HEF activities according to the standard format required.</li>\r\n 	<li>Perform other tasks as required.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Qualifications and Requirements:</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Completed Bachelor Degree or at least 2 years experiences</li>\r\n 	<li>Computer skills (Word, Excel, PowerPoint)</li>\r\n 	<li>Communication skill in English and Khmer</li>\r\n 	<li>Experience in data collection and/or assisting in any research/survey</li>\r\n 	<li>Strong interpersonal skills, demonstrated ability to work well with the poor and rural areas</li>\r\n 	<li>Analytical skills, Self-motivated and results oriented</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nThe deadline for applications is April 08th, 2016. All interested candidates can submit their applications by sending CV and cover letter indicating working station as above mentioned to: hr@pbhcam.org or submit a hard copy to the PBH offices on the 3rd floor, # 10, street 214, Sangkat Chey Chum Neas, Khan Daun Penh, Phnom Penh, Cambodia. Women are encouraged to apply. Only shortlisted applicants will be contacted.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="bg_job_color">\r\n\r\n<strong>Secretary for PBH executive director and CAMeHIN</strong>\r\nPBH is looking for Internship to be worked as a secretary for PBH executive director and CAMeHIN, and will be based at PBH office in Phnom Penh.\r\n\r\n<strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Act as secretary for Executive Director</li>\r\n 	<li>Act as secretary for CAMeHIN</li>\r\n 	<li>Assist PBH team for admin and finance work</li>\r\n 	<li>Assist CAMeHIN team members in doing CAMeHIN activities in Cambodia such as meetings/workshops etc</li>\r\n 	<li>Prepare and organize CAMeHIN hour on monthly basic</li>\r\n 	<li>Facilitate with AeHIN Cambodian members to find topics for CAMeHIN hour</li>\r\n 	<li>Facilitate to get more members to attend CAMeHIN hour and/or AeHIN hours</li>\r\n 	<li>Attend regular AeHIN hour</li>\r\n 	<li>Prepare and disseminate CAMeHIN reports and/or newsletters</li>\r\n 	<li>Ensure up to date PBH and CAMeHIN information and activities in CAMeHIN website, facebook and tweeter</li>\r\n 	<li>Monitor results of the project and conduct data quality audit at the field level</li>\r\n 	<li>Perform other tasks as required.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Qualifications and Requirements:</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Experience related accountant /admin</li>\r\n 	<li>Experience in ICT work and/or public health</li>\r\n 	<li>Good in English and Khmer</li>\r\n 	<li>Good in using computer and other ICT tools</li>\r\n 	<li>Good communication skills</li>\r\n 	<li>Good attitude</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nThe deadline for applications is Jan 31, 2015. Candidates interested in applying for the position should forward their CV’s together with a covering letter to: hr@pbhcam.org or submit a hard copy to the PBH office on the 3rd floor, # 10, street 214, Sangkat Chey Chum Neas, Khan Daun Penh, Phnom Penh, Cambodia. Only shortlisted applicants will be contacted.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="bg_job">\r\n\r\n<strong>Health Equity Fund Monitors</strong>\r\nThrough USAID Social Health Protection Project, PBH is looking for 2 (Two) appropriately qualified national candidates to fill the positions of Health Equity Fund Monitor who will based in <b>Bantheay Mean Chey (1 position)</b> and <b>Kandal (1 Position)</b>.The selected candidates will work under the supervision of the Health Financing Technical Officers, and she/he will be responsible for monitoring ongoing Health Equity Fund (HEF) activities in their target areas.\r\n\r\n<strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Oversee HEF Contract implementation based on established evaluation methodology</li>\r\n 	<li>On a monthly basis, monitor HEF activities are given area using the tools and methodologies of the HEF system</li>\r\n 	<li>Conduct household interviews and review of HEF documentation entering results into a computerized reporting database</li>\r\n 	<li>Create a monthly report of findings related to monitoring of HEF activities according to the standard format required</li>\r\n 	<li>Perform other tasks as required</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Qualifications and Requirements:</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Completed Bachelor Degree or at least 2 years experiences</li>\r\n 	<li>Computer skills (Word, Excel, PowerPoint)</li>\r\n 	<li>Communication skill in English and Khmer</li>\r\n 	<li>Experience in data collection and/or assisting in any research/survey</li>\r\n 	<li>Strong interpersonal skills, demonstrated ability to work well with the poor and rural areas</li>\r\n 	<li>Analytical skills, Self-motivated and results oriented</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nThe deadline for applications is December 20th, 2015. All interested candidates can submit their applications by sending CV and cover letter indicating working station as above mentioned to: hr@pbhcam.org or submit a hard copy to the PBH offices on the 3rd floor, # 10, street 214, Sangkat Chey Chum Neas, Khan Daun Penh, Phnom Penh, Cambodia. Women are encouraged to apply. Only shortlisted applicants will be contacted.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="bg_job_color">\r\n\r\n<strong>M&amp;E Advisor</strong>\r\nCurrently PBH is seeking 1 (one) appropriately qualified candidate to fill the position of Monitoring &amp;Evaluation Advisor (M&amp;E Advisor) for the USAID Quality Health Services project in Phnom Penh. This position is responsible for leading the Monitoring &amp; Evaluation Team and tasks for the USAID Quality Health Services project. This position is a key staff position of the Quality Health Services project and subject to USAID approval.\r\n<strong>Work Site / Based in:</strong>\r\n\r\nBased at URC Quality Health Services project office in Phnom Penh office with often traveling to provinces.\r\n\r\n<strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Lead and manage the Monitoring &amp; Evaluation team for the Quality Health Services project</li>\r\n 	<li>Oversee data collection and reporting of program performance indicators</li>\r\n 	<li>Lead the implementation of baseline, follow-up and evaluation studies</li>\r\n 	<li>Ensure availability and quality of routine performance monitoring data</li>\r\n 	<li>Synthesize data on project performance and RMNCHN developments into user-friendly reports and advocacy briefs to facilitate use by project management, RGC, and other partners</li>\r\n 	<li>Train partners in research, monitoring, and evaluation methods</li>\r\n 	<li>Oversee and supervise M&amp;E Team to perform M&amp;E tasks of QHS project</li>\r\n 	<li>Revise the project M&amp;E plan (MEP) as needed, ensure alignment with project direction, strategy and activities, selection of indicators, and agreement on annual targets</li>\r\n 	<li>Prepare M&amp;E information for all USAID reports including semi-annual, annual and bi-monthly reports</li>\r\n 	<li>Undertake statistical analysis and interpret the result of baseline, annual survey and quality assessment for the project. Analyze and produce summaries of results in consultation with component coordinators, cross cutting teams, and regional directors</li>\r\n 	<li>Provide technical assistance to the MOH on the National Level 2 Quality Assessment, in collaboration with the SHP project</li>\r\n 	<li>Monitor results of the project and conduct data quality audit at the field level</li>\r\n 	<li>Perform other tasks as required.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Supervision role:</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Supervise M&amp;E officers on Quality Health Services (QHS) project: currently there are 4 M&amp;E officers on the project.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Qualifications and Requirements:</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Master degree in public health, medical science or social science</li>\r\n 	<li>At least 10 years experiences in public health, M&amp;E and/or research, and NGOs</li>\r\n 	<li>Strong experience in quantitative research and design of data systems/management information systems. Thoroughly conversant with internationally used measures of health impact and coverage such as the indicators used in the Demographic and Health Surveys</li>\r\n 	<li>Experience with tracking quality improvements and using data to help improve quality and comprehensiveness of services is also desired</li>\r\n 	<li>Good interpersonal skills</li>\r\n 	<li>Ability to work as part of a team or independently</li>\r\n 	<li>Prior Cambodian experience and Khmer language fluency is strongly preferred. Prior experience with Monitoring and Evaluation of USAID-funded programs or similar international donor programs is strongly preferred</li>\r\n 	<li>Fluency in written and spoken English is essential.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nThe deadline for applications is September 25, 2015. Candidates interested in applying for the position should forward their CV’s together with a covering letter to: hr@pbhcam.org or submit a hard copy to the PBH office on the 3rd floor, # 10, street 214, Sangkat Chey Chum Neas, Khan Daun Penh, Phnom Penh, Cambodia. Only shortlisted applicants will be contacted.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="bg_job">\r\n\r\n<strong>Software Installation</strong>\r\nCurrently PBH is seeking an appropriately qualified candidates to fill the position of Programmer based in Phnom Penh, this position assist Health Informatics Programmer Team Leader in developing health related database systems.\r\n<strong>Work Site / Based in:</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Phnom Penh/ Travel to province</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Window and Ubuntu Linux Installation and Configuration</li>\r\n 	<li>Hardware Installation and Configuration (Printer, Barcode and Webcam Camera)</li>\r\n 	<li>Review and Testing Software and Hardware</li>\r\n 	<li>Hardware Quality Check</li>\r\n 	<li>Provide end user support</li>\r\n 	<li>Other tasks as required</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Qualifications and Requirements:</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Bachelor degree of Computer Science/Information Technology or equivalent</li>\r\n 	<li>1 year experienced with software installation and configuration</li>\r\n 	<li>Have experienced with hardware configuration</li>\r\n 	<li>Have experienced with web application and web browser problem solving</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nThe deadline for applications is August 7th, 2015. Candidates interested in applying for the position should forward their CV’s together with a covering letter to: hr@pbhcam.org or submit a hard copy to the PBH office on the 3rd floor, # 10, street 214, Sangkat Chey Chum Neas, Khan Daun Penh, Phnom Penh, Cambodia.\r\n\r\n<center>Women are encouraged to apply. Only shortlisted applicants will be contacted.</center></div>\r\n<div class="bg_job_color">\r\n\r\n<strong>Volunteer Secretary for CAMeHIN in Cambodia</strong>\r\nPartnership for Better Health (PBH) is an organization in Cambodia. PBH is looking for a volunteer to be worked as a secretary for CAMeHIN in Cambodia.\r\n<strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Act as secretary for CAMeHIN</li>\r\n 	<li>Assist CAMeHIN team members in doing CAMeHIN activities in Cambodia such as meetings/workshops etc</li>\r\n 	<li>Prepare and organize CAMeHIN hour on monthly basic</li>\r\n 	<li>Facilitate with AeHIN Cambodian members to find topics for CAMeHIN hour</li>\r\n 	<li>Facilitate to get more members to attend CAMeHIN hour and/or AeHIN hours</li>\r\n 	<li>Attend regular AeHIN hour</li>\r\n 	<li>Prepare and disseminate CAMeHIN reports and/or newsletters</li>\r\n 	<li>Ensure up to date CAMeHIN information and activities in CAmeHIN website, facebook and tweeter</li>\r\n 	<li>Perform other tasks as required</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Qualifications and Requirements:</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Experience as programmers/developers in PHP, MSQL etc</li>\r\n 	<li>Experience in ICT work and/or public health</li>\r\n 	<li>Good in English and Khmer</li>\r\n 	<li>Good in using computer and other ICT tools</li>\r\n 	<li>Good communication skills</li>\r\n 	<li>Good attitude</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nThe deadline for applications is <b>July 30th, 2015</b>. Candidates interested in applying for the position should forward their CV’s together with a covering letter to: <a href="mailto:hr@pbhcam.org">hr@pbhcam.org</a> or submit a hard copy to the PBH offices on the 3rd &amp; 4th floor, # 10, street 214, Sangkat Chey Chum Neas, Khan Daun Penh, Phnom Penh, Cambodia. Only shortlisted applicants will be contacted.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="bg_job">\r\n\r\n<strong>Programmer Consultant</strong>\r\nPartnership for Better Health (PBH) is an organization in Cambodia. PBH is looking for a programmer consultant to be worked in PBH office in Phnom Penh.\r\n<strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Review and upgrade PBH website</li>\r\n 	<li>Update news in PBH websites and media</li>\r\n 	<li>Develop other websites as needed</li>\r\n 	<li>Perform other tasks as required</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Qualifications and Requirements:</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Experience as programmers/developers in PHP, MSQL etc</li>\r\n 	<li>Experience in ICT work and/or public health</li>\r\n 	<li>Good in English and Khmer</li>\r\n 	<li>Good in using computer and other ICT tools</li>\r\n 	<li>Good communication skills</li>\r\n 	<li>Good attitude</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nThe deadline for applications is <b>July 30th, 2015</b>. All interested candidates can submit their applications by sending CV and cover letter indicating working station as above mentioned to: <a href="mailto:hr@pbhcam.org">hr@pbhcam.org</a> or submit a hard copy to the PBH offices on the 3rd floor, # 10, street 214, Sangkat Chey Chum Neas, Khan Daun Penh, Phnom Penh, Cambodia.\r\n\r\n<center>Women are encouraged to apply. Only shortlisted applicants will be contacted.</center></div>', 'Job and Career', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '1761-revision-v1', '', '', '2018-06-23 12:06:13', '2018-06-23 12:06:13', '', 1761, 'http://localhost/bkpbhcam/2018/06/23/1761-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
